liblangen (LANguageGENerator)

http://libalf.informatik.rwth-aachen.de/

(c) 2008,2009 Lehrstuhl Softwaremodellierung und Verifikation (I2), RWTH Aachen University
          and Lehrstuhl Logik und Theorie diskreter Systeme (I7), RWTH Aachen University
(c) 2010 David R. Piegdon


liblangen is a C++ library for generating (regular) languages by means
of finite automata or regular expressions. currently it consists of

	1) an equally distributed DFA generator

	2) a RegEx generator

	3) a NFA generator

	4) an enumerator for DFAs

DEPENCENCIES:

	liblangen only has two dependencies:
	the GNU multiple precision arithmetics library GMP and its C++
	interface (libgmp and libgmpxx).

